cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.CC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with the analysis of the performance limit of lattice sequential decoder for lattice space-time coded MIMO channel. This falls under the domain of information theory.
2. cs.SI (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the computational complexity of the lattice sequential decoder and how it can be reduced. This falls under the domain of systems and control.
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with the analysis of the diversity-multiplexing tradeoff (DMT) under lattice sequential decoding. This is relevant to networking and internet architecture as it helps in understanding the performance of wireless communication systems.
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the computational complexity of the lattice sequential decoder and how it can be reduced. This falls under the domain of computational complexity.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with the analysis of the performance limit of lattice sequential decoder for lattice space-time coded MIMO channel. This is relevant to multimedia as it helps in improving the performance of wireless communication systems used for multimedia applications.
